Concurrent Validity
Correlation coefficients were evaluated for each of the scales used (Table 3) ZEF and CSQ (−0.29), ZEF and TMPS (−0.31), and CSQ and TMPS (0.50) were significantly
correlated (P<.0o1). Higher CSQ scores indicate higher satisfaction, whereas higher ZEF scores indicate more extreme Zoom fatigue.
