Incremental Validity
The hierarchical linear regression revealed a highly significant relationship between the CSQ and TMPS. Incremental validity is significant; it is only with the CSQ. A hierarchical linear regression was conducted for the TMPS with CSQ and ZEF scales entering the model. The coefficient for CSQ was significant (P<.001) but not for ZEF (P=.06), indicating that only CSQ accounted for additional variance in the TMPS.
Multicollinearity was within normal limits for all models. With TMPS and CSQ entered the model, CSQ significantly accounted for additional variance in the TMPS (P<.001) (Table 4). With the ZEF entered the model, no additional variance was accounted for (P=.06).
